TITLE: Voters head to polls in Maryland, where Trump’s clout over GOP faces a test in gubernatorial primary
SUMMARY: Former President Donald Trump isn’t on the ballot on Tuesday in Maryland’s primaries, but the candidate he's backing is one of the co-front-runners in the GOP gubernatorial race

TITLE: Ohio Senate showdown: New Ryan ad accuses Vance of using opioid non-profit to further ‘political career’
SUMMARY: A new TV ad by Ohio Democratic nominee Rep. Tim Ryan targets rival J.D. Vance over a non-profit organization the now-Republican nominee set up five years ago

TITLE: Activist group that offered bounties for Supreme Court justices' locations targets Congressional Baseball Game
SUMMARY: A Washington, D.C., activist group that's already targeted Supreme Court justices after the abortion ruling is calling for protesters to shut down the Congressional Baseball Game.

TITLE: Judge denies Steve Bannon's request for delay to criminal contempt trial
SUMMARY: Former Trump administration White House aide Steve Bannon's defense team requested a one-month delay before his criminal contempt trial begins, but Judge Carl Nichols said no.

TITLE: Reps. Comer, Stefanik push Mayorkas on funding of NGOs for migrant releases into US
SUMMARY: House Republicans, including the ranking member of the House Oversight Committee, are requesting answers of the use of NGOs in migrant releases at the southern border.

TITLE: Blogger paid by Dem candidate who targeted Mayra Flores defends sexist attacks, other racist posts
SUMMARY: A Texas blogger who targeted Mayra Flores and was paid by Vicente Gonzalez's campaign has a history with racist words that target both Hispanic and African Americans.

TITLE: Immigrants bussed from Texas and Arizona welcome in nation's capital, say residents
SUMMARY: Immigrants who crossed the border illegally and were bused to Washington, D.C. from Texas and Arizona are welcome in the nation's capital, residents say.

TITLE: Ex-de Blasio aide blasts him as 'annoyingly condescending,' said she was 'terrified' he could run NYC: Book
SUMMARY: Lis Smith, a former top aide to Democratic House candidate Bill de Blasio, slammed the former NYC mayor as "childish" and unfit to lead in her new memoir outTuesday.

TITLE: GOP senators criticize Biden’s foreign trip, warn threat to US due to Afghanistan withdrawal, Iran aggression
SUMMARY: Republican senators are criticizing Biden's foreign trip to Israel and Saudi Arabia, saying that he didn't achieve any objectives and put the U.S. in a more vulnerable position when it comes to Iran.

TITLE: House measure says Congress obligation to call convention for balance budget amendment
SUMMARY: Rep. Jodey Arrington, R-Texas, is set to introduce a measure on Tuesday requiring Congress fulfill an obligation in calling a convention of the states.

TITLE: Bennie Thompson tests positive for COVID-19; Jan. 6 hearing to proceed
SUMMARY: Bennie Thompson, the chairman of the House select committee investigating the Jan. 6 attack on the U.S. Capitol, announced he has tested positive for COVID-19.

TITLE: John Kerry's family private jet emitted over 300 metric tons of carbon since Biden took office
SUMMARY: A private jet owned by the wife of John Kerry, who President Biden made climate envoy in January 2021, has emitted a whopping 715,886 pounds of carbon dioxide since Biden took office.

TITLE: House inked $96K deal to give staff premium access to meditation app
SUMMARY: The U.S. House cited the coronavirus pandemic and the January 6 incident as its reason for spending $96,000 in taxpayer money on a meditation app.

TITLE: Nikki Haley teases White House bid while slamming Biden on Iran
SUMMARY: Nikki Haley, former U.S. Ambassador to the UN, teased a possible White House bid on Monday during a speech that was critical of President Biden's appraoch to Iran.

TITLE: Biden to sign executive order to build on efforts to bring American hostages home
SUMMARY: President Biden is signing an executive order that will give the U.S. government the ability to impose sanctions on foreign nations that wrongfully detain Americans.

TITLE: Olena Zelenska, Ukraine's first lady, set to address US Congress after meeting with Blinken
SUMMARY: Ukrainian First Lady Olena Zelenska met with U.S. Secretary of State Antony Blinken ahead of her address to Congress later this week.

TITLE: House to vote on same-sex marriage, abortion rights, contraceptive coverage over SCOTUS concerns
SUMMARY: House Democrats have set up a series of votes to codify certain marriage and abortion rights brought into question following the U.S. Supreme Court's overturning of Roe v. Wade.

TITLE: Amid concerns about Biden's age in 2024, lawmakers say voters should judge president on performance
SUMMARY: President Biden's age has been a major subject of recent news stories, but GOP and Democrat lawmakers say people should judge him by his performance instead.

TITLE: Dem senators call for Biden 'unchained' on climate executive action, despite recent Supreme Court EPA ruling
SUMMARY: Some Senate Democrats are telling President Biden that to take major unilateral steps on climate change, despite a recent Supreme Court ruling on the EPA.

TITLE: Nikki Haley: Biden’s push for new Iran Deal will ‘come back to bite’ the US, Israel if not faced with strength
SUMMARY: Former U.N. Ambassador Nikki Haley told Fox News Digital during an exclusive interview that the Biden administration should focus on hitting Iran with strength.
